Usage: add_decomp_filler [-help] -bottom_edge_endcap {cell_name}
                         -core_column_cell {cell_name}
                         -core_row_cell {cell_name ...} [-offsetx <float>]
                         [-offsety <float>] [-power_domain <name>]
                         [-prefix <name>] -stepx <float> -stepy <float>
                         -top_edge_endcap {cell_name}
                         -vertical_edge_endcap {cell_name}

-help                              # Prints out the command usage
-bottom_edge_endcap {cell_name}    # specify CA-break end cap cell for rows, to
                                   # make bottom_edge of endcap face core
                                   # (string, required)
-core_column_cell {cell_name}      # specify CA-break filler cell for inserting
                                   # into columns (string, required)
-core_row_cell {cell_name ...}     # specify list of CA-break filler cells
                                   # inserted in the core rows horizontally
                                   # (string, required)
-offsetx <float>                   # specify the offset added to first step in
                                   # horizontal direction, in microns
                                   # (float, optional)
-offsety <float>                   # specify the offset added to first step in
                                   # vertical direction, in microns
                                   # (float, optional)
-power_domain <name>               # Power domain for which CA-break filler
                                   # cells are to be inserted (string, optional)
-prefix <name>                     # Prefix of decomp cells, 
                                   # (string, optional)
-stepx <float>                     # specify the decomposition step in
                                   # horizontal direction, in microns
                                   # (float, required)
-stepy <float>                     # specify the decomposition step in vertical
                                   # direction, in microns (float, required)
-top_edge_endcap {cell_name}       # specify CA-break end cap cell for rows, to
                                   # make top_edge of endcap face core
                                   # (string, required)
-vertical_edge_endcap {cell_name}  # specify CA-break end cap cell inserted at
                                   # the left and right edges as end caps
                                   # (string, required)